<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0229 </DOCNO><TEXT>A heat and power plant includes an internal combustion engine drivingan electric generator and having its exhaust gases conveyed to a CFB-boileras primary fluidizing gas. The boiler supplies steam to a turbine drivinga further electric generator. The exhaust steam from the turbine is condensedin a heat exchanger forming part in a district heating plant. A heatexchanger heats the feed water to the boiler by means of waste heat fromthe internal combustion engine.</TEXT></DOC>